''See also'' [[Levant]].
==English==
===Etymology 1===
Transferral use of [[Levant]], from French [[levant#French|levant]].  Compare French [[faire voile en Levant]] ‘be stolen away’.

====Pronunciation====
[[IPA]]: /lɪ'vænt/

====Noun====
'''levant'''
# [[disappearing]] or [[absconding]] after losing a bet

====Verb====
'''levant'''
# to [[abscond]] or run away, especially to avoid paying money or debts
#:*'''1922''': He died of a Tuesday.  Got the run.  '''Levanted''' with the cash of a few ads. — James Joyce, ''Ulysses''

===Etymology 2===
From French [[levant#French|levant]].

====Pronunciation====
[[IPA]]: /'lɛvənt/

====Adjective====
'''levant'''
# ''(Heraldry)'' [[rising]], of an animal

